Title - VanEck Goes Huge on Bitcoin, Strategy Stays Unshaken, XRP Flashes Bullish: Jan 10 Crypto News
Date - 2026-01-10
Content - The cryptocurrency landscape on January 10, 2026, is buzzing with significant developments across institutional adoption, regulatory progress, long-term price outlooks, and platform innovations. Here's a roundup of the key headlines shaping the market today, highlighting both Bitcoin's corporate strength and broader ecosystem momentum.
MicroStrategy's (Now Strategy) Massive Bitcoin Treasury Proves Resilient
Strategy (formerly MicroStrategy) continues to dominate corporate Bitcoin holdings, with its treasury reaching 673,783 BTC as of early January 2026. Recent purchases, including around 1,286 BTC for approximately $116 million, have pushed the total value to roughly $60-63 billion (depending on spot prices around $90,000+ per BTC).
Analyses show this position provides robust coverage for the company's annual dividend needs (estimated at around $823 million), offering 2.7 years of operational runway in severe market downturns before any Bitcoin sales would be required. This self-funding model, bolstered by strong USD reserves (over $2 billion) and minimal reliance on sales, underscores Strategy's Bitcoin-centric strategy as a hedge against volatility.
VanEck's Ultra-Bullish Long-Term Bitcoin Forecast
Asset manager VanEck has released an aggressive outlook in its Long-Term Capital Market Assumptions report, projecting Bitcoin could reach $2.9 million per coin by 2050 in its base-case scenario.
In a hyper-adoption "hyper-Bitcoinization" bull case ‚Äî where Bitcoin captures significant shares of global trade settlement (up to 20%) and domestic GDP ‚Äî the price could soar to $53.4 million. Even the bear case sees BTC at $130,000. This forecast positions Bitcoin as a maturing reserve asset, driven by institutional integration and central bank interest.
U.S. Senate Advances Crypto Regulation with Clarity Act Vote
A pivotal moment for U.S. crypto regulation is approaching: The Senate Banking Committee has scheduled a vote on the Clarity Act for January 15, 2026.
This bipartisan legislation aims to establish a clear framework for digital assets, splitting oversight between the SEC and CFTC, defining security vs. commodity status, and addressing market manipulation concerns. Some members of Congress have disclosed Bitcoin purchases ahead of the vote, fueling speculation about positioning. Proponents argue it could reduce manipulation risks by 70-80% and unlock greater institutional participation if passed.
BNY Mellon Enters Tokenized Real-World Assets with On-Chain Deposits
Major custody giant BNY Mellon (with $57.8 trillion in assets under custody) has launched tokenized deposits on its Digital Assets platform. This service creates on-chain representations of client bank deposits, enabling 24/7 programmable transfers for collateral, margin, and settlements ‚Äî all while keeping funds within the regulated banking system.
Participants include major players like ICE, Citadel, Ripple, and Circle. This marks a significant bridge between traditional finance and blockchain, supporting real-time institutional cash flows without relying on external stablecoins.
Pump.fun Revamps Creator Fees to Fix Incentive Skew
Solana-based memecoin launchpad Pump.fun has announced a major overhaul of its creator fee system to address criticisms that prior models skewed incentives toward low-effort launches over active trading.
The update introduces creator fee sharing, allowing distribution across up to 10 wallets, post-launch ownership transfers, and revocation of update authority. Future changes will shift toward market-driven mechanics where traders influence fee justification. The announcement, from co-founder Alon after a long hiatus, sparked a 10%+ jump in the $PUMP token.
XRP Shows Bullish Technical Signals Amid Price Pressure
Ripple's XRP is displaying promising technical patterns, including a rare 5-day MACD Golden Cross (where the MACD line crosses above the signal line with positive histogram momentum).
This signal has historically preceded significant rallies, and analysts are watching $2 as critical support. While facing a potential retest, some forecasts eye $2.75 short-term and higher targets like $4-8 by end-2026, contingent on sustained momentum and broader adoption.
These stories reflect a maturing crypto ecosystem in early 2026 ‚Äî from corporate Bitcoin resilience and bold price visions to regulatory clarity and institutional blockchain integration. Stay tuned as the January 15 Clarity Act vote and ongoing market dynamics could set the tone for the year ahead!
